# 📈 Portfolio Optimization

This notebook-driven case study explores portfolio construction through the lens of financial data science, using historical stock data to simulate and evaluate investment scenarios.

## 📊 Key Objectives

- Normalize and allocate capital across multiple assets
- Simulate 10,000 portfolio weighting combinations
- Evaluate performance using cumulative return, volatility, and Sharpe Ratio
- Identify the optimal risk-adjusted portfolio

## 📁 Files Included

- `Portfolio Optimization.ipynb` – the main analysis notebook
- `AAPL.csv`, `AMD.csv`, `MSFT.csv`, `ORCL.csv` – daily historical pricing data

## 🧠 Skills Demonstrated

- Financial data wrangling with pandas
- Return, volatility, and Sharpe Ratio calculations
- Monte Carlo simulation for portfolio weighting
- Risk-return tradeoff visualization with matplotlib
- Insight communication in Jupyter format
